commitResults.messageTitle: Add Rabbit.java which is the class of the robot Rabbit.
Add function AddToList() to Rabbit.java where Rabbit keeps the user's input in a list.
Deleled Duke.java Added Task.java as a class of task noted down by Rabbit Added functions list(), mark() and unmark() Changed addToList() and main()
Added derived classes of Task: Todo, Deadline and Event. Added functions in Rabbit to create tasks of different types. Changed task to abstract
Fixed bugs in unmark and main function in Rabbit Changed input.txt EXPECTED.txt and runtest.sh to test Rabbit
Added exception classes: RabbitException, MarkUnmarkException and AddToListException Changed mark, unmark, addToList and main methods in Rabbit to handle exceptions
Added DeleteException clsss Added delete method in Rabbit to enable deleting a task Changed input and EXPECTED to test delete method
Change formatting of the code
Add save feature so that the list is kept in ./data/data.txt whenever there is a change in the lsit.
Change the implementation of the time of Task from String to LocalDataTime.
Add Parser.java, Storage.java, TaskList.java, Ui.java. Change methods in Rabbit.java.
Add all files into packages:Rabbit, Rabbit.RabbitException, Rabbit.util and Rabbit.Task.
Add Gradle support.
Add unit tests ParserTest and TaskListTest to test Parser and TaskList respectively.
Add javadoc to some public methods.
Change codes style according to coding standard.
Add Find method in TaskList to enable the user to find a task with keywords.
Add GUI to Rabbit using javaFX. Delete Ui.java as old UI system is no longer needed.
Add Assertions to TaskList class
commitResults.messageBody:
Assertions are good to detect bugs.

Let's add assertions in delete, mark and unmark methods in TaskList to
ensure that the task to be operated on is not null. Even though the methods
that are calling these methods throw exceptions when the task to be operated
is null, it is safer to use assertions as future modifications may result
in bugs that cannot be detected by the old method.

commitResults.messageTitle: Parse: use String.split() to replace old method
commitResults.messageBody:
Old methods in Parse split the string using for loop which is slow and
cumbersome.

Let's use String.split() is used to make the methods shorter.

Additional change package name according to naming convention.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add methods to edit a task content and time
commitResults.messageBody:
It is useful to be able to change a task's content and time without
deleting and recreating it.

Let's add edit() method in TaskList and parseEdit() in Parse to
implement this new feature.

commitResults.messageBody:
The GUI needs to be improved to look better.

Let's clip the avatar into a circle and change the colour of the box.
